157 #ifndef _MSC_VER
158 # define G_HAVE_ISO_VARARGS 1
159 # define G_HAVE_GNUC_VARARGS 1
160 # define G_HAVE_GNUC_VISIBILITY 1
161 
162 /* gcc-2.95.x supports both gnu style and ISO varargs, but if -ansi
163  * is passed ISO vararg support is turned off, and there is no work
164  * around to turn it on, so we unconditionally turn it off.
165  */
166 #if __GNUC__ == 2 && __GNUC_MINOR__ == 95
167 #  undef G_HAVE_ISO_VARARGS
168 #endif
169 
170 #define G_HAVE_GROWING_STACK 0
171 
172 #else /* _MSC_VER */
173 # define G_HAVE_ISO_VARARGS 1
174 #endif /* not _MSC_VER */
175 
176 #if defined(__SUNPRO_C) && (__SUNPRO_C >= 0x590)
177 # define G_GNUC_INTERNAL __attribute__((visibility("hidden")))
178 #elif defined(__SUNPRO_C) && (__SUNPRO_C >= 0x550)
179 # define G_GNUC_INTERNAL __hidden
180 #elif defined (__GNUC__) && defined (G_HAVE_GNUC_VISIBILITY)
181 # define G_GNUC_INTERNAL __attribute__((visibility("hidden")))
182 #else
183 # define G_GNUC_INTERNAL
184 #endif

196 #define GUINT32_TO_LE(val)  ((guint32) (val))

199 #define GINT64_TO_LE(val)   ((gint64) (val))
200 #define GUINT64_TO_LE(val)  ((guint64) (val))
201 #define GINT64_TO_BE(val)   ((gint64) GUINT64_SWAP_LE_BE (val))
202 #define GUINT64_TO_BE(val)  (GUINT64_SWAP_LE_BE (val))
203 #define GLONG_TO_LE(val)    ((glong) GINT32_TO_LE (val))
